launch.name: Starlink-21 (v1.0)
launch.details: This mission launches the 21st batch of operational Starlink satellites, which are version 1.0, from LC-39A or SLC-40. It is the 22nd Starlink launch overall. The satellites will be delivered to low Earth orbit and will spend a few weeks maneuvering to their operational altitude. The booster is expected to land on an ASDS.
